	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="2" facs="R 6456-27 (206).jpg"/>
			<p><!--{{Franklin Mott Gunther}}, The Situation of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> in
          <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798549/romania.html">Romania</placeName>,
          <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/683506/bucharest.html">Bukarest</placeName>,
        25.1.1939, S. 2, 5f., 10:</p>
      <p>Records of the U. S. Department of State relating to internal affairs of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798549/romania.html">Romania</placeName> 1910-1944,
        Wilmington, Del. 1981 (Mikrofilm-Edition): Dokument 871.4016 JEWS/119.--></p>
			<p>A <q>revivication of the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-454">Iron Guard</orgName>
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-964" type="subject">movement</term></q> did not eventuate; rather,
				the legionary leaders <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">have been shot</term> and
					the<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-964" type="subject"> movement’s</term> strength, both actual and
				potential, is greatly diminished. But the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-381" type="subject">Nazi
				</term>shadow still looms large. Whether the <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_germans">German</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-662" type="subject">threat</term> is a controlling or only a
				contributory factor, the fact is that the plight of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864"
					type="subject">Jews</term> in this country has grown worse and their <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-829" type="subject">fears</term> are greatly increased.</p>
			<p>The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948" type="subject">Government</term> can scarcely be called, as
				compared with the <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000930">Goga</persName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948" type="subject">Government</term> a year ago, strongly <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-329" type="subject">anti-Semitic</term>, but it ‘recognizes the existence
				of a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-351" type="subject">Jewish problem</term>’ and many are constrained
				to feel that although the <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000930">Goga</persName> and <persName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000084">Cuza</persName> program was openly and violently <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-329" type="subject">anti-Jewish</term> the actual effect of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-337" type="subject">measures</term> and methods employed by the present
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1063" type="subject">regime</term> is more severe. It is true that
				there is no out-and-out <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-346" type="subject">pogrom</term> and that <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948" type="subject">Governmental</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-339" type="subject">regulation of the Jews</term> is, on the surface,
				relatively slight, but pressure, obstacles, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-332" type="subject"
					>discriminations</term> – all of these forms of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-642" type="subject"
					>persecution</term> are becoming noticeably more numerous. [...]</p>
			<pb n="5" facs="R 6456-27 (209).jpg"/>
			<p>The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-815" type="subject">attitude</term> of the <orgName
					ref="#ehri_dr_government_romanian">Romanian Government</orgName> is, then, that this surplus <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">population</term> of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1149" type="subject">non-citizen</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> must go; there is to be no <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-346" type="subject">pogrom</term>, no violence, no brutality, but <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1173" type="subject">they must go</term>. Until a place is found for <pb
					n="6" facs="R 6456-27 (210).jpg"/> them and an arrangement is made for them to get there they will probably have a hard time. As
				to the others, the 800,000 who have established their <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1147"
					type="subject">citizenship</term>, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948" type="subject"
					>Government</term> points to their <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1147" type="subject"
					>citizenship</term> as a guarantee of the same treatment as accorded to others, although admitting that <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> ‘will probably not be admitted to the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">higher positions</term>’. [...]</p>
			<pb n="10" facs="R 6456-27 (214).jpg"/>
			<p>The <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_romanians">Romanians</term> are not, on the whole, a harsh or vindictive <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term>; they are, rather, tolerant and
				easy-going. I feel, therefore, that although the program of getting rid of what are termed the ‘surplus’ <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> will probably in any case be retained,
				there is not much likelihood of such a degree of violence or severity being employed as would call down strong <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-984" type="subject">criticism or general protest</term> from the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-173" type="subject">outside world</term>.</p>
